Food and drink
Melidice is known for many fabulous foods.
including the simple "Cupids Pie" which is made of
chicken, spinach, and carrots as well as the
exquisite Eldiburg Truffle, a 7 layer chocolate cake.
Religion
The kingdom of Melidice serves under a theocracy
so we belelive the Melidice Royal family has been sent
to us from the gods, however there has been known
to be other religions such as the followers of Kila
Although not illegal to practice another religion,
anyone who proposes hostile changes to the popular
sphere will be repimanded and publicly shamed.
Social Life
There are many festivals that take place during the
year, most popular being Eldin's Day in which we
celebrate the life and times of King Eldin the Grey.
Founder of the Melidice Family. (Mar. 13th)
Another favorite festival that we celebrate is
Drekinfein (Oct 12) in which we pray to the spirits
for a good harvest and make merry under The Wine Moon.
Eductaion
Young students, if not born to farming families,
typically learn arithmatic, and history of The
Melidice Family.
Though not much is known about them, children born to
families that follow the God Kila, tend to learn
extra ciricular arcane arts, out of the norm.
Any student, not of Kila, can seek arcane education,
that typically falls under the healing arts, however
one can also learn phsycic and transmutitive arts as
well at Willwick's School of the Arcane.

The History of Mipsing
Mipsing is Kingdom Melidice's favorite sport! Played
Typically by prisoners who committed attempt of murder
on high ranking Melidicians; The king, royal family,
preists, government officials, etc.
Though anyone can challenge someone to play it! Though
it is not only immoral to decline a challenge, but also
illegal!
Mipsing wasfirst played after King Chritio had found
Queen Mipsing kissing his Grand Wizard Yilian the Wise.
Chritio challenged the wizard to the first game and
the rest is history!
Set Up
Two teams, each comprising of equal players up to 12
stand on either side of the feild, it is their goal
to send spiked mace heads across the feild to rack up
as many points as possible.
How to Win
The game lasts 1 hr. each team has to throw the mace
heads at either theree opposing team's targets, susp-
ended on poles or at the opposing team themself. The
two lower goals gains 2 pts. body shots at anyone but
team captain counts as 4 pts. body shots at the
team captain gains 6 pts. a kill of anyone that's not
the team captain (since their typically prisoners,) 8
pts. however the killing of a team captain is illegal.
And whoever thows the killing mace head so will suffer
the consenquence of losing the game, as well as a jail
sentence.
this is all subjegated to change when put into
consideration that all players are prisoners in which
their sentence wouldn't be worsened.
Punishment of Loss
Since King Chritio was the first to win the game, he
punished his ex Grand Wizard to have his hand crushed
by the last Mace Head thrown, thusly rendering his
magic abilities useless, and thus his position of
Grand Wizard was revoked and given to his granddaughter
who he'd been training High Priestess-
